All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ConsoleInterface
The ConsoleInterface class represents a console-based user interface that provides methods to display messages, input integers, and input strings.
Controller
The class is an abstract class that provides a general interface for all controllers in the application.
Database
This class represents the methods to initialise and update the database.
FYPCoordinator
This class represents a FYP Coordinator who can supervise everything in the system.
FYPCoordinatorController
This class represents a controller for a FYP Coordinator in the FYP Registration System.
FYPCoordinatorView
The FYPCoordinatorView class provides methods for displaying information about FYP Coordinators in a console-based user interface.
FYPRSA
The FYPRSA class is the main class that initialises the FYP Registration System Application and runs the main controller.
IApproveRequest
The IApproveRequest interface defines methods to approve or reject a request.
ICreateRequest
This interface defines the method signature for creating a request.
MainController
The class is responsible for handling the main menu of the FYP Registration System Application (FYPRSA).
Project
This class represents a Project in the system.
ProjectStatus_Enum
This enum represents the different possible statuses for a project in the FYP Registration System.
ProjectView
The ProjectView class provides methods for displaying information about projects in a console-based user interface.
Request
This class represents a Request in the system.
RequestStatus_Enum
This enum represents the different possible statuses for a request in the FYP Registration System.
RequestType_Enum
This enum represents the different types of requests that can be made in the FYP Registration System.
RequestView
The RequestView class provides the methods to display the information related to different requests.
Student
The Student class represents a student in the system.
StudentController
This class represents a controller for a Student in the FYP Registration System.
StudentView
The StudentView class provides methods for displaying information about Students in a console-based user interface.
Supervisor
This class represents a Supervisor who can supervise projects in the system.
SupervisorController
This class represents a controller for a Supervisor in the FYP Registration System.
SupervisorView
The SupervisorView class provides methods for displaying information about Supervisors in a console-based user interface.
User
The User class is an abstract class that serves as the parent class for all user types in the FYP Registration System.
View
The View class is an abstract class that represents a view in a console-based user interface.
